
[1]connivance

   CONNIVANCE, n. [See Connive.] Properly, the act of winking. Hence
   figuratively, voluntary blindness to an act; intentional forbearance to
   see a fault or other act, generally implying consent to it.

   Every vice interprets a connivance to be approbation.
